U.S. termed World's Biggest Gangster
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article brands the U.S. as an unprecedented gangster, the world's worst robber as it came into being with the disposition and nature as a gangster.
 It says: The Korean peninsula has witnessed a vivid manifestation of the U.S. aggressive and brigandish nature. The last Korean war was the most typical brigandish war of aggression, state-sponsored terrorism perpetrated by the U.S. imperialists in the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the ceasefire the U.S. imperialists have incessantly resorted to the reckless military threat and blackmail against the DPRK and moves to start a new war against it, persistently raising a hue and cry over "threat" from somebody. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. brigandish nature finds a clear expression in the fact that it has persistently pursued sanctions and blockade and interference in others' internal affairs to strangle those countries aspiring after independence, socialism and progress. It is evidenced by the recent renewed passage of a bill on sanctions against Syria through U.S. Congress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. brigandish nature can be also proved by the fact that it is meddling in the internal affairs of other countries, assessing the "human rights situation" there with "human rights standards" of its own style and pulling them up over that issue as it pleases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. unilateral acts, defiant of even international law, only bring to light its true colours as an international gangster. 
 It is due to the U.S. brigandish acts that the international arena witnesses the abnormal and complicated situation where justice and progress are trampled underfoot and peace and stability disturbed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Progressive humankind should clearly see through the aggressive and brigandish nature of the U.S. and struggle against it.

Increased Defence Capability Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- The U.S. war of aggression against Iraq and the subsequent development afford a serious lesson to the people aspiring after independence and peace.
 Minju Joson today says this in a signed commentary carried one year after the U.S. start of military invasion against Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Iraqi war was an inevitable product of the U.S. imperialists' aggressive nature and mode of existence peculiar to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has already been well known to the world that the United States selected Iraq as its target of invasion long ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has left no means untried to bring Iraq under its control after singling it out as a stronghold of strategic importance for realizing its strategy of world domination as it is located in the region very favorable to it not only from the military and strategic point of view but from the economic and geographical viewpoint. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Iraqi war clearly proved that the UN Charter and international laws can not play any role in deterring the arbitrary and high-handed practices of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Powerful defence capability of one's own is only the best deterrence to check the invasion and war moves openly committed by the U.S. in different parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the physiology of the U.S. to become coward before the strong and ferocious before the weak. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when a country reacts to the U.S. imperialists' ceaseless moves for aggression and war with strong defence capability, can it protect its sovereignty and, furthermore, defend global peace and security, it concludes.

DPRK, First Tax-free Country
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- March 21 is the 30th anniversary of the promulgation of the law on abolishing the tax system for good and all in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Since the law was put into effect, the DPRK has become the first tax-free country in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government, regarding it as the supreme principle of their activities to promote the well-being of the people, have always paid deep attention to making all the working people be evenly well off and improving their living conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the country's economic conditions were difficult after the war, the government took various measures to systematically reduce the people's tax burden. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Juche 44(1955) the income tax of workers and office employees and the tax burden of handicraftsmen, entrepreneurs and businessmen were reduced considerably, and the agricultural tax-in-kind went down to 20.1 percent on an average. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Later, even the dramatically reduced agricultural tax-in-kind and income tax of workers and office employees were totally eliminated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the historic law "On Abolishing the Tax System" adopted at the 3rd Session of the 5th Supreme People's Assembly in 1974, the tax system, which had existed for thousands of years, was finally liquidated and the people's long-cherished desire was realized satisfactorily.

National Symposium on Koryo Medical Science Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- A national symposium on Koryo medical science was held at the Grand People's Study House on March 17 and 18 to mark the 25th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "On Developing Traditional Korean Medicine".
 Prof. and Dr. Choe Chang Sik, vice-minister of Public Health, said at the symposium that the work serves as guidelines indicating a bright way of developing Koryo medical science. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented there were several theses that referred to the successes made in the efforts to carry out the tasks set forth in the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed panel discussions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 38 papers on the research into scientific diagnosis and effective methods of treatment of diabetes, advanced stomach cancer, imperforated thrombotic vascular inflammation were appreciated at the panel of internal treatment and surgery in the field of traditional Koryo medicine, at least 30 papers on the acupuncture treatment of eye-proptosis caused by hyperthyroid and polyneuritis at the panel of acupuncture and more than 30 papers on the successes made in newly clarifying ingredients and medicinal effect of Koryo medicine at the panel of essential drugs and Koryo medicine.

Truth about Crimes Related to Additional Troop Dispatch to Iraq Disclosed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- The Information Department of the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea on March 12 issued a white paper disclosing before the whole world the truth about the crimes related to the additional troop dispatch to Iraq despite the unanimous opposition of the people from all walks of life.
 According to the white paper, the additional troop dispatch to Iraq is a crime committed by the U.S. in a premeditated manner to meet its national interests at the sacrifice of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. singled out south Korea, its colony, as the first target of its operation to recruit mercenaries needed for undertaking its war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. set media in motion in a bid to realize the additional dispatch of troops to Iraq. It created an atmosphere of pressure and dispatched war hawks to south Korea to put repeated pressure on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. coercive demand for troop dispatch clearly reminds one of the second order for troop dispatch to Vietnam and means a forcible requisition order to drive south Korean troops as a shock brigade and mercenaries in its efforts to realize its ambition to build a uni-polar world dominated by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The additional troop dispatch is a product of the pro-U.S. treacherous acts of the "Grand National Party" that took the lead in the U.S. moves for troop dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ultra-right conservative forces acted more rashly when the prospect of additional troop dispatch was becoming gloomier owing to the protest of the people resolutely defying the U.S. pressure and the submissive acts of the pro-U.S. sycophantic elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP's pro-U.S. sycophantic treacherous forces became more desperate in their moves to put into practice the additional troop dispatch at a time when it was censured by the international community and its allies, too, rejected its demand for troop dispatch to Iraq after the disclosure of the fact that the U.S. invaded Iraq on the basis of false information. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conservative press is fanning up an atmosphere for troop dispatch, spreading a rumor that the number of soldiers wanting to be dispatched to Iraq is increasing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The additional troop dispatch to Iraq fully revealed before the international community the ugly colors of south Korea as a complete colony of the U.S. and its war servant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the U.S. began to force south Korea to additionally dispatch troops in September last year, the people of all social standings kindled a torch of the all-people struggle against the troop dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their struggle against the troop dispatch mounted higher, occasioned by Rumsfeld's visit to south Korea aimed to put pressure on it to additionally dispatch troops to Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the pro-U.S. right-wing conservatives passed the "motion on additional troop dispatch to Iraq" through the "National Assembly" in spite of such opposition and protest of the people, they turned out in a massive struggle with bitterer resentment.
 The massive struggle against the additional troop dispatch to Iraq is an eruption of the people's will to defend their interests and not to repeat the tragic destiny at the time of the Vietnamese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The attack of the anti-U.S. resistance forces on the U.S. troops and the troops of its allies has been further intensified in Iraq since Bush declared the end of the Iraqi war and this resulted in killing 772 GIs and wounding 1,048 others in December last year alone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A miserable lot is awaiting the south Korean troops to be dispatched to Iraq as was the case with those who were dispatched to Vietnam. The troop dispatch to Vietnam left at least 5,000 persons dead and over 16,000 wounded. Many soldiers died of the aftermath of the defoliant spread by the U.S. after their return home and more than 50,000 victims of its aftermath are dying. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is chiefly to blame for the additional troop dispatch to Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people from all walks of life should wage a more dynamic anti-U.S., anti-war struggle to get the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces withdrawn from south Korea to the last one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the people should judge the 16th "National Assembly" which decided on the additional troops dispatch to Iraq and totally eliminate the chief culprits of the troop dispatch from the political arena by completely burying all the pro-U.S. treacherous forces of the "Grand National Party" in the coming "general election".

DPRK's Self-Defensive Deterrent Force Enough to Counter Any U.S. Preemptive N- Attack
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 19 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement
Friday denouncing the "reception, staging, onward movement and integration" (RSOI) and Foal Eagle joint military exercises the U.S. and the south Korean war hawks are going to stage from March 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has a self-defensive deterrent force powerful enough to cope with any U.S. preemptive nuclear attack and wipe out aggressors to the last man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. "policy of strength" is sure to prove ineffective in face of the great Songun politics and the deterrent force based on it and the provocateurs are bound to meet the fate of forlorn wandering spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee vehemently denounces the projected joint military exercises of the U.S. and its followers as an intolerable military provocation against the DPRK and an outright challenge to the desire and wish of all the Koreans and world peace-loving people for detente and peace on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had the second round of the six-way talks on the nuclear issue come to an end than the U.S. declared its plan to stage large-scale war maneuvers against its dialogue partner. This clearly shows that it seeks to invade the DPRK by force, while paying lip-service to "dialogue" and "peace." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is nobody's secret that the U.S. has massively shipped into south Korea ultra-modern military hardware tested in the Afghan and Iraqi wars, after rounding off "new operation plan 5026" for the invasion of the DPRK, and recently conducted even an exercise of evacuating families of U.S. servicemen in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces are bringing the dark clouds of a nuclear war to hang over the Korean peninsula. This compels the army and the people of the DPRK to keep a high degree of vigilance against these moves. They are firmly determined to mete out a merciless punishment to the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should immediately halt its reckless moves to provoke a war against the DPRK, clearly understanding that strength is not all-cure and the Korean peninsula is neither Iraq nor Afghanistan.
